HEADWORD: Fritfly
<hw>Frit"fly`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small dipterous fly of the genus <gen>Oscinis</gen>, esp. <spn>O.
vastator</spn>, injurious to grain in Europe, and <spn>O. Trifole</spn>,
injurious to clover in America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

